A report on this issue was prepared in 2011 by the Centre for Problem Analysis and Study for Public Administration.
Specialists analysed the reports of the Ministry of the Interior and Rosstat, criminal records and public data on arms portals.
The vast majority of illegal weapons, the researchers explain, come from the army and law enforcement agencies.
Half of the weapons on the black market were found there "because of the employees whose work is related to the weapons," the report explains.
According to researchers, 17% of weapons come from places of military conflict, 14% are stolen at the time of manufacture and 5% come from "hidden searches".
A seller and consultant at an armory who asked to keep anonymity ensures that for a long time no one has bought the weapons found by these specialists in the clandestine search; they are too old.
