We can only live there at very high altitude or in the orbit of Venus... in space.
We began to focus on the issues of reproduction in space by focusing on flora.
Half a century ago, we were experimenting on plants.
Four generations of small peas grown in orbit did not differ in any way from terrestrial varieties.
Then, insects, small reproductive drosophilic flies, were placed in orbit.
In 1979, quail eggs were sent into space to see how an embryo developed in weightlessness.
We get a perfectly normal chick at the exit.
Then the problems begin.
" The problem is related to the fact that the chick has to find support, he has to get on his feet and start moving," explains the director of the laboratory of the Institute of Medical-Biological Problems of the Russian Academy of Sciences (IMBP) Vladimir Sychev.
By not finding any support, the chicks were agitated in a disorderly way.
And after 10 hours, the newborns saw their instincts completely overrun.
The chicks did not react to light or sound.
Unfortunately, they would simply die after four days.
"We peeled their eyes twice, then we gave up, because it is simply impossible to work with them there," explains Vladimir Sychev, noting the failure of the experiment with chicks in space.
The last biological "miniature ark" with animals was sent to orbit 16 years ago.
The experiments will continue in the spring of 2013.
However, the biosatellite "Bion" will only board species of the same sex.
There was an experiment with rats sent with their fetuses into space.
In principle, nothing supernatural was discovered.
" It was still biosatellites, and then it's the only experience, and we have to do this kind of research, " notes Vladimir Sychev.
After landing, the space rats gave birth to their offspring.
However, reproductions are not yet possible directly in space.
It's not a big deal.
By losing their usual environment, animals are no longer able to realize their sexual instincts.
Unlike beasts, man is capable, in principle.
Homo sapiens possess abstract thinking, he is able to create a suitable emotional background.
This type of experience is not carried out for ethical reasons.
But women have been in space for 50 years.
The biggest risk was taken by Terechkova.
And the female organism is what humanity has most precious.
Our seagull flew and no one on Earth could tell if it would hold after a flight into space.
If she could have given birth to a child after the robbery.
