The father of the child, Andrian Nikolayev was also a cosmonaut.
In 1988, the second cosmonaut woman Svetlana Savitskaya, having been in orbit twice and even working in an extra-vehicle environment, gave birth to a son.
However, the risk persists.
We have few, even very few cosmonauts who have had nothing and who give birth to a healthy offspring after long flights.
