The head of the ISC (Superior Institute of Public Finance Control) said: "The control of pseudo-independent work (in Czech "Švarc system") failed because of politicians.
In the area of public procurement, the Czech Republic has competent inspectors and high-quality legislation but is lagging behind in its implementation.
This is what Miloslav Kala, Vice-President of the Higher Institute of Public Finance Control, said in an interview for Aktuálně.cz.
