"I will not retire, I will die here because the volcano is my whole life," Unainik says by opening his mouth well, revealing several missing teeth.
The eldest of his five children, 30 years old, also works as a sulphur carrier.
Time passes, but the perpetual misery from generation to generation one of the most difficult trades in the world: the one made by the human mules of the Kawah ljen volcano.
