For the time being, this judgment is not being respected.
This is a problem between a South American country and a Central American country.
Conflicts are inevitable, but they must be overcome by the will to move forward together.
They must be solved as a whole in order to overcome them and move forward.
At the same time, he expressed his confidence in the proper resolution of the maritime boundary dispute between Peru and Chile in the same court and stated that it is "beneficiary for Latin America to refer to international bodies if both countries agree to accept such a firm judgment".
Referring to the possibility of his nomination as a candidate for the future presidential elections in Ecuador, in order to run for a third consecutive term, he pointed out that he saw this possibility "with great optimism and joy, although sometimes it is quite difficult".
Correa assured that if he lost the primary school in February 2013, he would withdraw from public life.
At the personal level, I have never been interested in power, but in situations as unfair as those of Ecuador, this socio-economic poverty can only be solved through political power.
